Date:  4/9/1849
Source:  Daily Southern Cross
Author:
Vol / Page:  2
Edition:
Quote:  One hundred and sixty Kauri spars, raised perpendicularly, form the frame-work of this singular pile, several of them are squared, and five of them from 90 to 100 feet high, to which smaller spars of from 10 to 15 feet are again added, bound firmly together by the strong vine Torotoro, making the total height of the turret in the centre from 115 to 120 feet, from which other 8 turrets, ranging from 70 to 80 feet, run the length of the erection.
